---
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="Reading — June Kim">
  <main>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Reading</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">Textbooks and papers, translated into runnable code with diagrams.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Foundations</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400"></th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Subject</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Source</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">License</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3">🐱</td>
            <td class="pr-3"><a href="/reading/category-theory/">Category Theory</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Bartosz Milewski</td>
            <td class="text-gray-400">CC BY-SA 4.0</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3">🎲</td>
            <td class="pr-3"><a href="/reading/game-theory/">Game Theory</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Jennifer Nordstrom</td>
            <td class="text-gray-400">CC BY-SA 4.0</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3">🎰</td>
            <td class="pr-3"><a href="/reading/probability/">Probability</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Grinstead &amp; Snell</td>
            <td class="text-gray-400">GFDL</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-3">📡</td>
            <td class="pr-3"><a href="/reading/info-theory/">Information Theory</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Shannon 1948 + Wikipedia</td>
            <td class="text-gray-400">Public domain + CC BY-SA</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Papers</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4"><a href="/reading/natural-breadcrumbs/">🍞 Natural Breadcrumbs</a> — 21 research papers decoded into plain English, runnable Python, and SVG diagrams.</p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Glossary</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Term</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">Learn</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Category</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Objects and arrows that compose with identity and associativity</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-01/">🐱 ch1</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Functor</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">A structure-preserving map between categories</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-07/">🐱 ch7</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Natural transformation</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">A map between functors that commutes with morphisms</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-10/">🐱 ch10</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Monad</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">A functor with return and join that lets effects compose</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-17/">🐱 ch17</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Adjunction</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Two functors that are almost inverses: free/forgetful, curry/uncurry</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-16/">🐱 ch16</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Yoneda lemma</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">An object is determined by how everything maps into it</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-14/">🐱 ch14</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Kleisli category</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Side effects compose when you change what "arrow" means</td><td><a href="/reading/milewski-04/">🐱 ch4</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Nash equilibrium</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">No player can improve by switching strategy alone</td><td><a href="/reading/nordstrom-06/">🎲 §6</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Dominated strategy</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">If A is always worse than B, rational players never use A</td><td><a href="/reading/nordstrom-04/">🎲 §4</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Mixed strategy</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Randomize over pure strategies to prevent exploitation</td><td><a href="/reading/nordstrom-09/">🎲 §9</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Prisoner's dilemma</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Rational self-interest leads to a collectively worse outcome</td><td><a href="/reading/nordstrom-12/">🎲 §12</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Entropy</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Expected surprise: H(X) = -sum P(x) log P(x)</td><td><a href="/reading/shannon-02/">📡 §2</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">KL divergence</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Surprise of Q when the truth is P. Not a distance</td><td><a href="/reading/shannon-05/">📡 §5</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Mutual information</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">How much knowing X tells you about Y</td><td><a href="/reading/shannon-04/">📡 §4</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Data processing inequality</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Processing cannot create information</td><td><a href="/reading/shannon-06/">📡 §6</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Markov chain</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Next state depends only on the current state</td><td><a href="/reading/grinstead-11/">🎰 ch11</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Bayes' theorem</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Update beliefs with evidence: posterior = likelihood x prior / evidence</td><td><a href="/reading/grinstead-04/">🎰 ch4</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3">Hoare triple</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">If P holds before c runs, then Q holds after</td><td><a href="/reading/staton-2025/">🍞 Staton</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3">Open game</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">A game with interfaces: inputs, outputs, and a coplay channel</td><td><a href="/reading/hedges-2018/">🍞 Hedges</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Further reading (external)</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Permissive-licensed sources worth reading directly. Pointers, not derivatives.</p>
    <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-1 mb-4">
      <li><a href="https://forallx.openlogicproject.org/">forall x: Calgary</a> — propositional and predicate logic (CC BY 4.0)</li>
      <li><a href="https://openlogicproject.org/">Open Logic Project</a> — formal proof systems, model theory (CC BY 4.0)</li>
      <li><a href="https://leanprover-community.github.io/logic_and_proof/">Logic and Proof</a> — induction, Lean-flavored proofs (Apache 2.0)</li>
      <li><a href="https://softwarefoundations.cis.upenn.edu/plf-current/index.html">Software Foundations vol. 2</a> — Hoare logic, weakest preconditions (MIT)</li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4"><a href="https://june.kim/books/">My book notes</a> — 52 posts, 2012-2023.</p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs">This site is licensed <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" class="underline hover:text-gray-400">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>. Fork it, build on it, keep it open.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs mt-1"><a href="https://june.kim" class="underline hover:text-gray-400">june.kim</a></p>

  </main>
</Layout>
